Apply to the EdMedia Program

attendeeData.Please explain the reasons for your inte: I have had precious little experience in integrating media into my teaching, so I am really a blank canvas. As such, I really have a great deal to learn and fell as though I will really benefit from this program as I try to transition from postdoc to faculty.
I think these tools would be useful in articulating information better to Faculty as well as in expanding my personal career skillset.
to enhance the skills for using multi-media for the development of instructional audio-visual content
I need to gain more experience in presenting the course materials while lecturing.

I think that media or technologies nowadays have become more communicative and thus more powerful for teaching and learning. However, I believe that the identification of where a particular medium fits along any specific educational dimension depends on how that medium is designed. Though the EdMedia Program, I wish I can learn how to use new media and technologies effectively to create value in teaching and learning as opposed to using them merely for the sake of digitalization.

As the research manager at SFU's Community Health Research Team, I engage with many diverse community groups and research participants under the SFU name. I would like to improve my skills in digital media in order to provide a more refined presentation of our outputs and also to find new ways to engage with the SFU community, including students and members of other faculties in order to increase our presence and liaise within our own organization.

I am a graduate student at Political Science department and for the last two semesters, I have been completing the co-op at SFU Budget Office as Communication and Training Coordinator. I have been involved in the development of training videos and materials using User Productivity Kit (Oracle) for more than 150 users across three SFU campuses. 

I greatly enjoy the process of planning and developing various training materials and use of digital media. I am looking into expanding my career options towards this sector upon the graduation. EdMedia is a great opportunity for me to acquire new skills and knowledge that can greatly contribute towards my career aspirations.
I want to make students' homework and readings more interactive.

attendeeData.Please explain the reasons for your inte: I am a special educator . Students with learning challenges grasp faster if learning is imparted via interesting powerpoints and other media tools . They are able to sustain theirs interest levels for a longer time .
Being a phd student and a teacher, I always need to use media for various presentations.

I'm interested in learning to better design teaching and promotional materials for our student workshops and leadership programming. Working in student engagement and retention, I have the opportunity to work with blended programming and taking the EdMedia course will give me the opportunity to enhance the in-person and online experience for students. I'm interested in creating trailer videos for a number of our programs as well as working in graphic design towards launching a restructured website increasing the accessibility for students, faculty and staff on experiential learning opportunities.

I would like to know various educational technology as a graduate student in Educational technology and learning design program. I also would like to get some ideas to develop learning tools to help students in a Japanese language course.

attendeeData.Please explain the reasons for your inte: I am starting my second term teaching at SFU (BUS 216) in September and have been assigned courses in Spring 2018 & Fall 2018, so I would like to improve my teaching skills for upcoming work.
attendeeData.How did you find out about the EMP progr: From a teaching colleague | TLC newsletter

attendeeData.Please explain the reasons for your inte: I do not use any media in my presentations but I see others who do and find it very effective.
I'm applying for a sessional instructor position and I believe this program could enhance my knowledge and skills in teaching courses.

I am looking for new ways to communicate with undergraduate students in Earth science courses. In particularly, want to engage first year students who have limited science background and may be intimated by some of the science content in introductory level courses..
Langara hopes to implement a similar programme so I want to see what SFU is up to!Q

attendeeData.Please explain the reasons for your inte: As a teacher and a student myself, I am usually interested in finding both teaching and learning strategies. Before becoming a PhD student in the Faculty of Education at SFU, I had approximately seven years of teaching experience at a university level in Thailand. Due to the progress in information technology nowadays, more and more students have changed their learning preferences. As a result, I hope that the EdMedia Program will be able to provide alternative and creative ways of how I may create and use educational media in order to conform to the changes of students' learning interests.
I want to explore the possibilities of teaching in various mediums online and in person.
